#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""{{AGENT_NAME}} ops digest — daily internal/technical report, emailed agent-account -> operator.

Deterministic (no LLM — raw facts are the point, unlike the morning brief's
synthesis). Reports the last 24h of background activity:

  * Cron health   — did each launchd job run + succeed (backup / meeting-reports /
                    github-docs-sync / morning-brief / meeting-prep / call reports /
                    yesterday's digest), from their logs, + the gateway process
  * Agent activity— sessions, tool calls, tokens, est. cost from state.db (by
                    source + model)
  * KB growth     — new docs / meetings / customers / people in 24h (Postgres)
  * GitHub sync   — last run's synced / pruned totals
  * Backup        — last bundle size + age
  * Memory stores — USER.md / MEMORY.md §-round-trip + size vs config limits
                    (Hermes only checks at WRITE time and tells nobody — a jammed
                    store surfaces here instead of recycling as chat errors)
  * Voice (Bland) — prepaid balance + total calls, so credit never dies mid-call

Rendered as a compact HTML email. Auto-allowed email-to-self cron (operator only).
Scheduled via launchd `ai.hermes.ops-digest` ~8:10am ET (just after the brief).
Smoke-test:  python ops_digest.py            (add --dry-run to skip the send)
"""
